cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.GR 

The paper deals with the problem of Single Image Super-Resolution (SISR), which is a well-known topic in computer vision and image processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a learning-based approach to solve the problem, which involves the use of deep neural networks, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. Additionally, the paper discusses the efficiency of the proposed method, which suggests that it may fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence and Robotics). The paper also mentions image sharpening and contrast enhancement, which are related topics in computer graphics and multimedia, making cs.MM (Multimedia) another possible category. Finally, the paper may also fall under cs.GR (Graphics) as it deals with image processing and enhancement.
